The  New York Knicks  hired Mark
Warkentien as director of pro player personnel, the National
Basketball Association team said in a statement.  Warkentien was formerly vice president of basketball
operations for the  Denver Nuggets . Heâ€™ll consult with team
president Donnie Walsh on the NBA draft, have scouting
assignments and will advise on personnel moves, the team said.  Warkentien previously worked in the NBA with the Portland
Trail Blazers, Cleveland Cavaliers and Seattle SuperSonics. He
also spent 11 years in the basketball operations department at
